<tr id="Fil2017" class="entry">
	<td>Fil, V., Kolodyazhnaya, M., Zvyagina, G., Bilych, I. and Zhekov, K.</td>
	<td>Piezomagnetoelectric effect in LiCoPO4 <p class="infolinks">[<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Fil2017','abstract')">Abstract</a>] [<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Fil2017','bibtex')">BibTeX</a>]</p></td>
	<td>2017</td>
	<td><font color="#006400">Physical Review B</font><br/>Vol. 96(18), pp. 180407(R)&nbsp;</td>
	<td><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevB.96.180407" target="_blank">DOI</a> &nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr id="abs_Fil2017" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: The piezomagnetoelectric effect is considered to be the appearance of a piezoelectric response caused by a magnetic field in magnetically ordered media. The possibility of its existence in antiferromagnets was predicted in the 1960's; however, attempts at its experimental detection were unsuccessful. In this Rapid Communication, our experiments confirm the appearance of the piezomagnetoelectric effect in a LiCoPO4 single crystal.</td>
