<tr id="abs_Zhuravleva2017597" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: A detailed theoretical study of the anomalous magnetovolume effect in the exchange-enhanced itinerant paramagnet YCo2 was carried out based on DFT calculations of the electronic structure in an external magnetic field and further complemented with the experimental data on the behavior of the magnetic susceptibility χ under high hydrostatic pressure. The calculations of the magnetic susceptibility and magnetovolume effect dlnχ/dlnV are in reasonable agreement with the experimental data, indicating the proximity of YCo2 to the ferromagnetic instability.</td>
