	<td><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.jmmm.2014.09.032" target="_blank">DOI</a> &nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr id="abs_Baranovskiy201596" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: The electronic structure of the antiferromagnetic Shastry-Sutherland compound GdB4 has been analyzed with density functional theory and the all-electron full-potential linearized augmented-plane wave (FP-LAPW) code. Different magnetic configurations, including the realistic dimer one, have been considered. The exchange interactions were found to be J1/kB=-12K and J2/kB=-2-0.8K, where, J1 and J2 are the diagonal exchange interaction and the exchange interaction along the edges of a square, respectively.</td>
