	<td>Karpinsky, D., Troyanchuk, I., Silibin, M., Gavrilov, S., Bushinsky, M., Sikolenko, V., Sirenko, V. and Tebbens, D.</td>
	<td>Crystal structure and magnetic exchange in La1-2xSr2xMn1-xSbxO3 (x ≤ 0.2) solid solutions <p class="infolinks">[<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Karpinsky20151006','abstract')">Abstract</a>] [<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Karpinsky20151006','bibtex')">BibTeX</a>]</p></td>
	<td>2015</td>
	<td><font color="#006400">Low Temperature Physics</font><br/>Vol. 41(12), pp. 1006-1010&nbsp;</td>
	<td><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1063/1.4937365" target="_blank">DOI</a> &nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr id="abs_Karpinsky20151006" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: The crystal structure and magnetic properties of the stoichiometric compounds La1-2xSr2xMn1-xSbxO3 (0.1 ≤ x ≤ 0.2) with manganese ions in the 3+ oxidation state are studied. These compounds exhibit rhombohedral structure at room temperatures, which transforms upon cooling into an orthorhombic structure without any signature of orbital ordering. The compounds with x ≤ 0.2 reveal a ferromagnetic ordering; their magnetization decreases with increasing the concentration of substitution ions. It is suggested that the observed ferromagnetism originates from the breakdown of orbital ordering and significant hybridization between the eg orbitals of Mn3+ and 2p orbitals of oxygen.</td>
