<tr id="abs_Panfilov2015528" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: Chemical bonds and their manifestations in the magnetism of ground-state multiferroic BiFeO<sub>3</sub> are studied theoretically. The magnetic properties of BiFeO<sub>3</sub> in the antiferromagnetic state and their dependences on hydrostatic pressure are studied experimentally and theoretically. These results indicate a substantial rise in the magnetic susceptibility χ of the compound under pressure with a characteristic pressure derivative dlnχ/dP ~ 3 × 10-2 GPa-1. A quantitative estimate of the magnetostriction is made on the basis of this value for the derivative and it is shown that a magnetostriction mechanism predominates in the interactions of the magnetic and electric subsystems of multiferroic BiFeO<sub>3</sub>.</td>
