<tr id="Sirenko2014" class="entry">
	<td>Sirenko, V. and Eremenko, V.</td>
	<td>The universality of the magnetization irreversibility line of metglasses and superconductors <p class="infolinks">[<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Sirenko2014','abstract')">Abstract</a>] [<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Sirenko2014','bibtex')">BibTeX</a>]</p></td>
	<td>2014</td>
	<td><font color="#006400">Low Temperature Physics</font><br/>Vol. 40(9), pp. 859&nbsp;</td>
	<td><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1063/1.4897012" target="_blank">DOI</a> &nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr id="abs_Sirenko2014" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: An analysis of the experimental data of the temperature dependence of metallic glass and superconductor magnetization. A common feature is the irreversibility of magnetization: below a certain temperature T*, under fixed field strength, magnetization varies during cooling within (MFC), and outside (MZFC) of a magnetic field. It is demonstrated that for all samples, the line T*(H) is universal, and corresponds to the theoretical dependence of de Almeida-Thouless (T* ~ H2/3) in all studied ranges of magnetic fields.</td>
</tr>
<tr id="bib_Sirenko2014" class="bibtex noshow">
<td colspan="7"><b>BibTeX</b>:
