	<td>Sirenko, V., Ibulaev, V., Shvedun, M. and Eremenko, V.</td>
	<td>Wide band XRD study of 2H-NbSe2 in a CDW-regime <p class="infolinks">[<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Sirenko2009','abstract')">Abstract</a>] [<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Sirenko2009','bibtex')">BibTeX</a>]</p></td>
	<td>2009</td>
	<td><font color="#006400">Journal of Physics: Conference Series</font><br/>Vol. 150(4), pp. 042186&nbsp;</td>
	<td><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1088/1742-6596/150/4/042186" target="_blank">DOI</a> &nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr id="abs_Sirenko2009" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: Albeit rather simple structure and ample experimental study of charge density wave (CDW) superconductor 2H-NbSe2 its behaviour in a CDW regime (TCDW 32.5 K, TSN 7.2 K) remains unclear. The relevance of the known mechanisms of CDW formation to this hexagonal modification of the niobium diselenide is not straightforward. Occurrence of the lock-in transition in this compound is still debated despite numerous structural investigations by means of diverse diffraction techniques. Here, we present Debye patterns measured in a detail at temperatures 8-35 K with different sources of X-ray irradiation and energy resolution of about 1eV. New features observed in the temperature range 15-30 K are discussed in terms of fluctuation-mediated phase transition.</td>
