</tr>
<tr id="abs_Bartoloḿ2008642" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: The magnetic properties of 2H-Nb Se2, a layered metal with a hexagonal structure of the crystal lattice, are measured, and the change of those properties after irradiation with high-energy electrons is investigated. It is shown that the main part of the magnetic susceptibility comes from the Pauli paramagnetism of free charge carriers. The low-temperature deviations from Pauli paramagnetism are explained by dangling interatomic bonds, which are present in small numbers even in the unirradiated samples.</td>
