<tr id="abs_Smirnov20071839" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: The specific heat at constant pressure and the velocity of sound in the SiC/Si biomorphic composite prepared from white eucalyptus wood are measured in the range 3.5-65 K and at 77 K, respectively. The heat capacity of the SiC/Si sample under investigation is calculated within three proposed models according to the Kopp-Neumann additivity rule.</td>
