<tr id="Zvyagin200011511" class="entry">
	<td>Zvyagin, A. and Zvyagina, G.</td>
	<td>Staggered magnetization and realization of Jahn-Teller-like effects <p class="infolinks">[<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Zvyagin200011511','abstract')">Abstract</a>] [<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('Zvyagin200011511','bibtex')">BibTeX</a>]</p></td>
	<td>2000</td>
	<td><font color="#006400">Physical Review B - Condensed Matter and Materials Physics</font><br/>Vol. 62(17), pp. 11511-11516&nbsp;</td>
	<td><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevB.62.11511" target="_blank">DOI</a> &nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr id="abs_Zvyagin200011511" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: A realization for the cooperative Jahn-Teller-like effect in low-dimensional quantum critical systems is proposed. We show that at low temperatures these systems are unstable with respect to the spontaneous appearance of alternating effective g factors, which also pertain to nonzero alternating distortions of ligands, surrounding magnetic ions. The effect is magnetic field-induced. The proposed effect is discussed in connection with recent experiments on effectively low-dimensional electron systems.</td>
