	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: The amorphous alloys Fe100-xBx are soft magnetic materials with a wide range of applications. In this article, data is presented, showing that the electronic structure is the least stable for the threshold hypoeutectic alloy Fe84B16 and the most stable for the eutectic one. This observation is in agreement with the idea of special, probably, quasicrystal, cluster structure of amorphous alloy Fe83B17.</td>
