</tr>
<tr id="abs_Belevtsev19971223" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: The transition from variable-range hopping conductivity to simple activated one (the Arrhenius law) is observed in single-crystal La2CuO4+δ) as the temperature is decreased below T ≃ 20 K. It is shown that this effect can be assigned to the presence of superconducting inclusions (of Tc = 15-20 K) in insulating sample. The existence of such inclusions may be related to the well-known phase separation for La2CuO4+δ.</td>
