	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: Magnetic susceptibility of RNi5 single crystals (R=Gd, Tb, Dy) was studied under uniform and uniaxial pressures at temperatures above TC. The uniform pressure derivatives of the paramagnetic Curie temperature Θ and the crystalline electric field parameter B0 2 appear to be small. On the other hand, Θ and B0 2 parameters display a large sensitivity to the uniaxial pressure due to related changes of c/a ratio. Ab initio electronic structure calculation was performed for GdNi5 to evaluate the volume derivative of TC.</td>
