	<td><font color="#006400">Czechoslovak Journal of Physics</font><br/>Vol. 46(SUPPL. 4), pp. 2153-2154&nbsp;</td>
	<td><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/BF02571068" target="_blank">DOI</a> &nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr id="abs_Fil19962153" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: We have measured the anisotropy of the spin reorientation fields in Nd2Cu04 single crystals from the magnetoelastic effects. For T &amp;gt;1.5K our experimental data can be understood it terms of the four-sublattice antiferromagnet nmdel and allow to estimate the relation between the phenomenological constants of the model. For T &amp;lt;1.5K we have found a manifestation of new spin-reorientation field stimulated phase transition. These transitions exist only in narrow range of the angles between the magnetic field and [100] directions and are connected most likely with the Nd spins.</td>
