	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: The magnetic susceptibility of UCu3Au2 and UCu3Au2 has been measured at 78 and 290 K under hydrostatic pressures up to 2 kbar. The pressure dependence of the susceptibility is correlated with the change in the paramagnetic Curie temperature. For both compounds the dΘ dP value was determined to be about -0.2±0.05 K kbar-1.</td>
