<tr id="abs_Grechnev1984287" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: Using nonlocal semi-empirical pseudopotentials, we calculate the electron energy spectrum of the compound Cd//3Mg at T equals 0. The detailed dependences of the density of electron states indicate significant differences between the band structures of Cd//3Mg and pure cadmium. We trace the evolution of the total energy of the crystal during the transition from cadmium to the disorder phase and then the ordered phase of Cd//3Mg. The energy of the band structure is shown to be a minimum in the order phase.</td>
