<tr id="grechnev1983" class="entry">
	<td>Grechnev, G.E.</td>
	<td>Effect of pressure and impurities on the electronic spectum of cadmium <p class="infolinks">[<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('grechnev1983','abstract')">Abstract</a>] [<a href="javascript:toggleInfo('grechnev1983','bibtex')">BibTeX</a>]</p></td>
	<td>1983</td>
	<td><font color="#006400">Fizika Nizkikh Temperatur</font><br/>Vol. 9(10), pp. 1060-1067&nbsp;</td>
	<td><a href="http://fnte.ilt.kharkov.ua/fnt/pdf/9/9-10/f09-1060r.pdf" target="_blank">URL</a>&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr id="abs_grechnev1983" class="abstract noshow">
	<td colspan="7"><b>Abstract</b>: Using semiempirical nonlocal pseudopotentials, calculation is made of cadmium electronic spectrum changes at helium temperatures under uniform and uniaxial compression, as well as when doping with isovalent impurities (magnesium and mercury). Local dampingpara meters are calculated for electronic states in Cd--(Mg) and Cd--(Hg). A number of electronic topological transitions are predicted at K and L symmetry points, and on Sigma symmetry line in the Brillouin zone. The relation between specific behavior of some physical characteristics of Cd--Mg and Cd--Hg alloys, as well as of pure Cd under pressure, and topological changes of the Fermi surface is discussed.</td>
